Johnny Manziel has been released from rehab after checking into a facility on January 28 . 
  The Cleveland Browns quarterback is out and ready to begin offseason workouts with the team on April 20 . 
  Manziel was in rehab for six weeks and said he was 'doing great' in the facility . 
  He entered rehab after his rookie season was marred by controversy over his drinking and partying . 
 